{
  "id": "RLSA-2026:4064",
  "title": "Important: postgresql:12 security update",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-03-09 18:01:13"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-03-23 18:11:09"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "PostgreSQL is an advanced object-relational database management system (DBMS).\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* postgresql: PostgreSQL missing validation of multibyte character length executes arbitrary code (CVE-2026-2006)\n\n* postgresql: PostgreSQL intarray missing validation of type of input to selectivity estimator executes arbitrary code (CVE-2026-2004)\n\n* postgresql: PostgreSQL pgcrypto heap buffer overflow executes arbitrary code (CVE-2026-2005)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
